# SkyWeb Analytics Change Log

This file carries the detailed implementation history so `README.md` can stay focused on current usage and architecture.

## DN-10 — Cutover and Legacy Consolidation

- Promoted `apps/web-dotnet/SkyWeb.Client` as the default SkyWeb client for local development and production build scripts.
- Preserved the original `apps/web` app as an explicit rollback baseline.
- Updated root package scripts:
  - `npm run web` -> `.NET` client.
  - `npm run build` -> `.NET` client build.
  - `npm run preview` -> `.NET` client preview.
  - `npm run web:legacy` -> original legacy client.
  - `npm run web:legacy:build` -> original legacy client build.
  - `npm run web:legacy:preview` -> original legacy client preview.
- Added `dotnet:clean` convenience script.
- Updated DN-10 README status, request-flow notes, local development commands, environment notes, and primary URLs.
- Updated DN validation checklist for post-cutover defaults.
- Updated `.env.example` and `SkyWeb.Client` README for the new primary client path.
- Kept alert evaluation intentionally SkyServer-owned.

## DN-9.5 — Pre-Cutover Cleanup and Documentation Lockdown

- Cleaned README around current status, request flow, and local development commands.
- Moved detailed history out of README and into this change log.
- Added DN validation checklist.
- Refreshed repo map and documentation notes.
- Confirmed repo zip hygiene expectations: exclude `bin/`, `obj/`, `dist/`, and `node_modules/`.

## DN-9.4.2 — Alert Overlay Polish and Indicator Chart Cleanup

- Added overlay mode selector: `Thresholds`, `Thresholds + events`, and `Off`.
- Defaulted detail charts to threshold overlays without event-marker noise.
- Split overlay counts into threshold count and event-marker count.
- Removed redundant single-indicator metric dropdown and `Selected: Value` pill.
- Adjusted ECharts rendering to reduce hover repaint artifacts.

## DN-9.4.1 — Alert Overlay Page Wiring Fix

- Restored page-level alert overlay loading for indicator detail pages.
- Restored page-level alert overlay loading for macro-view detail pages.
- Confirmed overlays appear on relevant chart surfaces when matching alert rules exist.

## DN-9.4 — Alert Overlays and Chart Annotations

- Added alert threshold overlays to ECharts detail charts.
- Added optional alert-event markers.
- Added severity-aware overlay styling and tooltip details.
- Kept dashboard mini charts clean by avoiding dense overlay rendering there.

## DN-9.3 — Chart UX Polish and Runtime Hardening

- Hardened the ECharts base wrapper lifecycle.
- Added resize handling through `ResizeObserver` with fallback behavior.
- Added chart loading, empty, and unavailable states.
- Improved date axis labels, numeric labels, tooltip filtering, and latest-point emphasis.

## DN-9.2 — Chart Architecture Extraction and Adapters

- Added reusable chart architecture under `components/charts`.
- Added adapters for indicator series, view series, dashboard charts, and alert overlays.
- Refactored compatibility wrappers so existing page call sites could remain stable.

## DN-9.1 — ECharts + D3 Chart Engine Foundation

- Added Apache ECharts and D3 dependencies.
- Replaced copied `.NET` lane SVG chart internals with ECharts renderers.
- Preserved parent component APIs.

## DN-8 — Alerts and Signal Center in C#

- Implemented native C# alert-rule endpoints.
- Implemented native C# alert notification and Signal Center endpoints.
- Left alert evaluation intentionally proxied to SkyServer.

## DN-7 / DN-7.1 — Saved Views and Dashboards in C#

- Implemented saved-view CRUD in C#.
- Implemented dashboard CRUD in C#.
- Implemented dashboard item management in C#.
- Stabilized saved-view/dashboard build warnings and compile behavior.

## DN-6 — Profile and Preferences in C#

- Implemented profile endpoints in C#.
- Implemented dashboard preference endpoints in C#.
- Implemented alert preference endpoints in C#.

## DN-5 / DN-5.1 / DN-5.2 — Auth and Macro Stabilization

- Implemented native C# auth endpoints.
- Mirrored opaque bearer-token session behavior with SHA-256 token hashes.
- Added permissions/session handling and auth middleware.
- Stabilized public macro series reads.
- Fixed PostgreSQL `regclass` materialization and numeric `NaN` handling.

## DN-4 — Public Macro REST Endpoints in C#

- Implemented public macro summary, view, latest-row, column, indicator, and indicator-series endpoints in ASP.NET Core/C#.
- Kept response contracts compatible with the React client.

## DN-0 through DN-3 — Parallel .NET Lane Foundation

- Preserved the pre-.NET baseline.
- Created `apps/web-dotnet` with `SkyWeb.Api` and `SkyWeb.Client`.
- Added health, DB health, Swagger, CORS, and PostgreSQL connection setup.
- Wired the copied client through `SkyWeb.Api` with proxy fallback during migration.

## Historical SkyWeb Feature Phases

- Phase 1: SkyWeb foundation, routing shell, package scripts, environment template, and API client.
- Phase 2: SkyServer public macro bridge.
- Phase 3: Macro Dashboard v1, view cards, drilldowns, tables, and indicator explorer.
- Phase 4: Auth shell and member layer prep.
- Phase 5: Dashboard chart polish and macro storytelling.
- Phase 6: Profile and preferences UI.
- Phase 7: Saved dashboards, watchlists, builder, viewer, and presentation mode.
- Phase 8: Macro alerts, evaluation history, notification queue, alert preferences, Signal Center, and alert-rule UX polish.
